Tragically, Bastien-Lepage's career was cut short when he passed away at the young age of 36. However, his influence on the art world continued to be felt, and his legacy as a skilled and empathetic painter lives on.

items.name: Mango Sticky Rice
items.description:
Mango Sticky Rice is meant to produce photorealistic images of various themes. I've tested with fantasy, scifi, landscapes, mechs, cybernetics, robots, women, men, etc. Sometimes the initial generation may look more like an illustration (particularly if the character or focus is far away), but using Loopback Scaler (my preferred method) or Highres fix will help pull it back to photorealism rather well.

One thing to note is that it can be difficult to generate a male character sometimes since so much training has a female bias. I highly recommend Zovya's Gender Slider to help with this.

Please note that the prompts shown for the images are the initial generation prompts. When using Loopback Scaler or upscaling, I modify the prompts to bring out or reduce certain features, and of course prompts become very simple for inpainting most of the time.

For final upscaling I use Ultimate SD Upscaler.

These are the two upscalers I use I this point:

4x-UltraMix Restore
UltraSharp

But others might like these as well:

Foolhardy Remacri
NMKD Siax 200k
NMKD Superscale SP 178000 G
lollypop

I almost exclusively use DPM++ 2M Karras for generation and upscaling through Ultimate SD Upscaler. I do swap to DDIM for Loopback Scaler though!

items.name: Lara Croft - Rise of the Tomb Raider
items.description:
I wanted to do is for a while. Lara Croft is one of my favorite video game character. In the reboot trilogy Rise Lara was the best for me. So I tried to capture the look by using my own screenshots for training. However due to my extreme reshade usage back then results are darker than usual. So I will give you some advice to mitigate it as much as possible.

Recommended settings : 0.65 - 0.75 weight with hiresfix 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler.Clip skip 2.

In the positive prompt add "(desaturated:1.08)". You might need to adjust the emphasizing.

In the negative prompt add "(two tone lighting)" and "(dimly lit)". It's preferrable but it helps to get clean results.

Finally you can use "LowRa" with negative values to brighten the results a bit more. Hope you like it :)

Support me on buymeacoffee if you like my work.

CFG: 7

Resolution: 512x512, 512x768, 768x512

<lora:reference sheet-model sheet:1> , reference sheet, model sheet, simple background,

Or

<lora:reference sheet-model sheet:1> , reference sheet, model sheet, simple background, (multiple views, [full body|from behind|from side|from front|close-up|upper body|portrait]:1),

You can experiment with other types of background if you don't want it to be simple. Training images were mostly based on white/grey and black backgrounds.
